{"key":"processedPost-9290772","value":{"id":9290772,"first":9289339,"last":9290901,"when":1227372969,"utime":"11/22/08 06:56 PM","content":"I would recommend any mushroom grower to purchase an extra cool mist humidifier and run it 24/7 in your house all winter.&nbsp; Try to get your indoor humidity to 40% to 50% and not only will you feel and breathe better, your energy bills will be much lower, since humid air holds the heat better than dry air.(thermal mass)<br /><br />With a given amount of moisture in the air, if you raise the temperature by 20F, the RH is roughly cut in half.&nbsp;  Therefore, if your outdoor dewpoints are in the single digits and you heat the house to 70F, your indoor humidity is extremely low, around 10% or even less.<br />RR","title":"Re: Worried about the RH."}}